Hey <%= @subscriber.greeting_name %>,

There is another trick to make your renders go faster.

It doesn't require expensive GPUs, or even a render farm. It doesn't have to
cost you anything. It's all about using the compute power you already have
smarter.

When you're rendering with Cycles, you start off with a grainy image. Over time,
the more samples are being computed, the better it looks. (obviously)

Often times though, some areas of the image are already looking nice and clean,
while other parts are still very grainy.

Wouldn't it be amazing if you could laser-focus that render power on those grainy
bits? In a "smart" way?

That's called Adaptive Sampling! Check out this article and video where I explain
all about this great Blender feature:
<%= article_url("render-smarter-in-blender-with-adaptive-samples") %>

Enjoy ☕️

- Richard

